<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-24T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8292: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-24T12:00:00-05:00">October 24,
                                1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>255. Your 511, October 23, 5 p.m. Department and Navy Department approve.
                            Navy Department states that captain possesses authority to make such
                            transfer. Please take complete and effective precautions that there be
                            no publicity.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>